<Content>Ultra modern and friendly hotel in great location My boyfriend booked for us to go to Barcelona for 2 nights at this hotel for my birthday. I initially looked the location of the hotel up on a map of Barcelona and thought it was a long way out of the centre......how wrong was I!! The location is perfect for exploring all of Barcelona's beautiful areas.We were welcomed by a very friendly member of staff on reception who spoke good english and was very helpful. Check-in was smooth and we were given the key card to our room. The interior of the hotel is ultra modern but not uncomfortable looking. Our room was big with a really lovely bathroom. The BEST SHOWER I have ever used in my life!! Air con was easy to use also as we were quite hot.You are a 2 min walk from the main line metro station which takes you to all the major areas, the metro is the best thing in barcelona for getting around, so cheap (10 euro for a 2 day pass) and so quick, there is a train every 5 minutes without fail.My best advice is the following:- Get the Barcelona Bus from Girona airport to the Arc de Triomf metro station and get the metro (2 stops) to Placa Espanya which is 2 mins from the hotel (20 euro return)- DO NOT GET A TAXI as we missed the bus on the way back and had to pay 120 euros!!!- Go to the beach at Barceloneta and eat lunch at one of the cafes- Go to the Picasso Museum and walk around the Gothic Quarter and have lunch near the Cathedral- Walk along Las Ramblas in the day and look at all the human statues and stalls (lots of animals for sale though which isn't very nice)- DO NOT EAT ON LAS RAMBLAS as they over charge, eat on one of the side roads, much nicer and cheaper- Shop and eat tapas on Passeig de Gracia- Walk up the road directly next to the hotel and watch the Magic Fountains at Castle Montjuic (shows 7pm - 9pm). Have a glass of Cava at the top and sit on the cool bobbly chairs (you have to see them)Overall, this hotel is perfect and I would definately stay there again. Can't wait for my nect trip. 
