<Author>willngrace
<Content>Great Location Great Location, Friendly staff, very young, however very few spoke english. Make sure you put a do not disturb sign on the door, for room cleaning staff will just knock and enter. It happened two days in a row. The rooms are sound proof and bathrooms were very clean! For those of you who need an iron, beware it is not provided, we ended up buying a small one for 9 euros, being that the laundry serve price is ridiculous!! 9 euros to iron a shirt!! Also we asked for an early wake up call and never got it. Luckily I had also set my ipod. The location is great. We're from NY, so the walk to Placa de Catalunya wasn't bad for us, about 20 min. However the Espana metro is a few minutes walk from the hotel. Over all, I would stay there again, it's on a major street, but not as hectic as las ramblas!! 
